# Twitter Sentiment Analysis Dataset

This folder contains the dataset used for training and evaluating models for Twitter sentiment analysis.

## Description

The dataset consists of tweets collected from Twitter's public API, along with corresponding sentiment labels. Each tweet is labeled with one of the following sentiment classes: positive, negative, or neutral. The dataset enables the development and evaluation of machine learning and natural language processing models for sentiment analysis on Twitter data.

## File Format

The dataset is stored in CSV (Comma-Separated Values) format.

## Data Attributes

1. `text`: The text content of the tweet.
2. `sentiment`: The sentiment label assigned to the tweet (positive, negative, neutral).

## Usage

This dataset can be used for various tasks related to sentiment analysis, including training classification models, evaluating model performance, and conducting research in the field of natural language processing. It is important to preprocess the text data appropriately, including tasks such as tokenization, removing stop words, and handling special characters or emojis, before training machine learning models.

## Note

- The dataset is provided for research and educational purposes only.
- When using the dataset, ensure compliance with Twitter's terms of service and data usage policies.
- Please respect user privacy and do not redistribute or share the dataset without proper authorization.

